Predictions from Box is really what drew me in to this particular method of ITC. A Franks Box built in March 2007 predicted a very specific military stike. I was hesitant to post the information at the time since it seemed inflammatory but was shocked to see most of it come true. Here&#39;s the link to what happened and what Franks Box predicted to a large extent.

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operation_Orchard

I told Frank about this and then dialog with him about other forecast led to a interview with George Noorey about Doomsday Predictions. After the interview it was stated by a listener that people will look for events that fits the prediction and Box forecast were unreliable. The forecast that we spoke about concerned a catastrophe on the East Coast of the United States that may result in loss of life in a tidal wave from the Atlantic ocean and possibly due to a meteor strike. However, with no meteors being tracked and no huge storm in weather forecast bearing down on the easy coast, it was a dicey prediction as it was August 14 and the prediction said the danger would be on the 15th but no year was given. Here&#39;s the link to that broadcast:

http://www.coasttocoastam.com/show/2009/08/14

At that point Frank and I knew at least we went public with information regarding a disaster and we provided specific information. Then that next day, August 15, a sudden storm developed into Tropical Depression Bill, intensified to Tropical Storm Bill, and formed a large eye. Within days, a newly dubbed Hurricane Bill would end the life of a 7-year-old girl who drowned after she, her father, and a 12-year-old girl were swept off a rocky ledge near Acadia National Park in Maine. Here&#39;s the link to info on that storm:

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hurricane_Bill_(2009)

-Bill


